
// This Hyperlambda code snippet demonstrates how to add nodes to a specific location in a data structure. It uses the [add] slot to append nodes at the specified path, and retrieves nodes using the [get-nodes] slot to fetch the [limit] and [offset] arguments from the [.arguments] node. This allows for dynamic modification of the data structure based on input arguments.
add:x:@data.connect/*/data.read
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/limit
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/offset
